Here is a sample input settings file used for this paper, with notes. The settings file is in JSON format, and no comments are allowed, so I provide here an explanation. The actual files used for the paper are includedin the github.

Note that all quotes are double quotes, and spaces and special characters must be avoided in sample and file names.

import scipy.stats as stats
import math
import numpy

def plot_mutation_step(axis, lib_name, rRNA_name, start_position, end_position, color, subtract_background=False, alpha=1,
                      ymin=-.01, ymax =0.1, linestyle='-'):
    library = ecoli_batch1_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    x = range(start_position, end_position+1)
    y = []
    for rRNA_position in x:
        nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
        if subtract_background:
            mutation_fraction = nuc.get_back_sub_mutation_rate()
        else:
            mutation_fraction = nuc.mutation_rate
        y.append(mutation_fraction)
    if subtract_background:
        axis.step(x, y, color=color, label='%s-%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name, library.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name), 
                  lw=1, alpha=alpha, linestyle=linestyle)
    else:
        axis.step(x, y, color=color, label='%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name), lw=1, alpha=alpha, linestyle=linestyle)
    plot.set_ylim(ymin,ymax)
    plot.set_xlim(start_position, end_position+1)
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['bottom'].set_visible(False)
    plot.set_ylabel('mutation fraction')
    
def plot_rt_stop_step(axis, lib_name, rRNA_name, start_position, end_position, color, subtract_background=False, alpha=1,
                     ymin=-1000, ymax=10000, linestyle='-'):
    library = ecoli_batch1_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    x = range(start_position, end_position+1)
    y = []
    for rRNA_position in x:
        nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
        if subtract_background:
            rt_stop_rpm = nuc.get_rt_stop_rpm()-nuc.get_background_nucleotide().get_rt_stop_rpm()
        else:
            rt_stop_rpm = nuc.get_rt_stop_rpm()
        y.append(rt_stop_rpm)
    if subtract_background:
        axis.step(x, y, color=color, label='%s-%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name, library.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name), 
                  lw=1, alpha=alpha, linestyle=linestyle)
    else:
        axis.step(x, y, color=color, label='%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name), lw=1, alpha=alpha, linestyle=linestyle)
    plot.set_ylim(ymin,ymax)
    plot.set_xlim(start_position, end_position+1)
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['bottom'].set_visible(False)
    plot.set_ylabel('RT stop RPM')

for lib_name in ['2_70S_UV_SSII_FL']:
    library = ecoli_batch1_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    for nuc in 'ATCG':

                                                        exclude_constitutive=True)]

import scipy.stats as stats
import math
import numpy
 
def plot_rt_stop_step(axis, lib_name, rRNA_name, start_position, end_position, color, subtract_background=False, alpha=1, 
                     ymin=-1000, ymax=10000):
    library = ecoli_batch1_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    x = range(start_position, end_position+1)
    y = []
    for rRNA_position in x:
        nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
        if subtract_background:
            rt_stop_rpm = nuc.get_rt_stop_rpm()-nuc.get_background_nucleotide().get_rt_stop_rpm()
        else:
            rt_stop_rpm = nuc.get_rt_stop_rpm()
        y.append(rt_stop_rpm)
    if subtract_background:
        axis.step(x, y, color=color, 
                  label='%s-%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name, library.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name), lw=1, alpha=alpha)
        plot.set_title('%s-%s' % (library.lib_settings.sample_name, library.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name))

import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np
def plot_correlation(axis, experiment, lib_nameX, lib_nameY, nucs_to_include='ATCG', color=mod_utils.black, 
                     subtract_background=False, exclude_constitutive=True):
    x = []
    y = []
    libX = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameX)
    libY = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameY)
    for rRNA_name in libX.rRNA_mutation_data:
        for position in libX.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides:
            nucX = libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            nucY = libY.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            if libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position).identity in 'AG' and not (exclude_constitutive and nucX.exclude_constitutive):
                if subtract_background:
                    valX = nucX.get_back_sub_mutation_rate()
                    valY = nucY.get_back_sub_mutation_rate()
                else:
                    valX = nucX.mutation_rate
                    valY = nucY.mutation_rate
                if valX>0 and valY>0:
                    x.append(valX)
                    y.append(valY)
    plot.scatter(x, y, color=color, s=2)
    rho, p = stats.spearmanr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    r, p = stats.pearsonr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    if subtract_background:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s-%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameX, libX.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s-%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY, libY.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name))
    else:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameX))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY))
    plot.set_yscale('log')
    plot.set_xscale('log')
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.annotate('rho=%.3f, r=%.3f, n=%d' % (rho, r, len(x)), xy=(.00002, .5), xytext=(.00002, .5))
    plot.set_xlim(.00001,1)
    plot.set_ylim(.00001,1)
    
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
colors = [mod_utils.black, mod_utils.reddishPurple, mod_utils.vermillion, mod_utils.bluishGreen]

plot = fig.add_subplot(221)
plot_correlation(plot, ecoli_batch1_datasets, '3_70S_UV_NAZ_SSII_FL', '4_70S_EFG_UV_NAZ_SSII_FL', nucs_to_include='AG', subtract_background=False)
plot = fig.add_subplot(222)

import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np
def plot_RT_MaP_correlation(axis, experiment, lib_nameX, lib_nameY, nucs_to_include='ATCG', color=mod_utils.black, 
                     subtract_background=False, exclude_constitutive=True):
    x = []
    y = []
    libX = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameX)
    libY = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameY)
    for rRNA_name in libX.rRNA_mutation_data:
        for position in libX.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides:
            nucX = libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            nucY = libY.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            if libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position).identity in 'AG' and not (exclude_constitutive and nucX.exclude_constitutive):
                if subtract_background:
                    valX = nucX.get_rt_stop_rpm()-nucX.get_background_nucleotide().get_rt_stop_rpm()
                    valY = nucY.get_back_sub_mutation_rate()
                else:
                    valX = nucX.get_rt_stop_rpm()
                    valY = nucY.mutation_rate
                if valX>0 and valY>0:
                    x.append(valX)
                    y.append(valY)
    plot.scatter(x, y, color=color, s=2)
    rho, p = stats.spearmanr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    r, p = stats.pearsonr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    if subtract_background:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s-%s RPM" % (lib_nameX, libX.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s-%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY, libY.get_normalizing_lib().lib_settings.sample_name))
    else:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s RPM" % (lib_nameX))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY))
    plot.set_yscale('log')
    plot.set_xscale('log')
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.annotate('rho=%.3f, r=%.3f, n=%d' % (rho, r, len(x)), xy=(.2, .9), xytext=(.2, .9))
    plot.set_xlim(.1,1000000)
    plot.set_ylim(.00001,1)

def make_sig_change_calls(lib_name):
    library = ecoli_batch1_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    #compute normalization factors
    exp_mutations = []
    ctrl_mutations = []
    for rRNA_name in library.rRNA_mutation_data.keys():
        for rRNA_position in sorted(library.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides.keys()):
            nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
            if nuc.identity in 'AG':
                exp_mutations.append(nuc.mutation_rate)
                ctrl_mutations.append(nuc.get_control_nucleotide().mutation_rate)
    exp_norm = numpy.mean(exp_mutations)
    ctrl_norm = numpy.mean(ctrl_mutations)
    
    protections = {}
    deprotections = {}
    for rRNA_name in library.rRNA_mutation_data.keys():
        positions = []
        reactivity_deltas = []
        z_factors = []
        for rRNA_position in sorted(library.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides.keys()):
            nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
            if nuc.identity in 'AG' and not nuc.exclude_constitutive:
                positions.append(rRNA_position)
                control_sub=(nuc.mutation_rate/exp_norm) - (nuc.get_control_nucleotide().mutation_rate/ctrl_norm)
                reactivity_deltas.append(control_sub)
                exp_error = nuc.get_error()/exp_norm
                ctrl_error = nuc.get_control_nucleotide().get_error()/ctrl_norm
                z = 1-(1.99*(exp_error+ctrl_error)/abs(control_sub))
                z_factors.append(z)
        reactivity_delta_mean = numpy.mean(reactivity_deltas)
        reactivity_delta_std = numpy.std(reactivity_deltas)
        scores = (numpy.array(reactivity_deltas)-reactivity_delta_mean)/reactivity_delta_std
        protections[rRNA_name] = [positions[i] for i in range(len(positions)) if abs(scores[i])>0 and z_factors[i]>0 and reactivity_deltas[i]<0]
        deprotections[rRNA_name] = [positions[i] for i in range(len(positions)) if abs(scores[i])>0 and z_factors[i]>0 and reactivity_deltas[i]>0]
    return protections, deprotections

all_prot_calls = {}
all_deprot_calls = {}
for lib_name in lib_names:
   all_prot_calls[lib_name], all_deprot_calls[lib_name] = make_sig_change_calls(lib_name)

import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np

#rewrite this to arbitrarily subtract any two libraries regardless of preferences file
def plot_correlation(axis, experiment, lib_nameX, lib_nameY, bground_nameX=None, bground_nameY=None, nucs_to_include='ATCG', color=mod_utils.black, exclude_constitutive=True):
    x = []
    y = []
    libX = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameX)
    libY = experiment.get_lib_from_name(lib_nameY)
    if bground_nameX is not None and bground_nameY is not None:
        bground_libX = experiment.get_lib_from_name(bground_nameX)
        bground_libY = experiment.get_lib_from_name(bground_nameY)
    for rRNA_name in libX.rRNA_mutation_data:
        for position in libX.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides:
            nucX = libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            nucY = libY.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            if bground_nameX is not None and bground_nameY is not None:
                back_nucX = bground_libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
                back_nucY = bground_libY.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position)
            if libX.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, position).identity in 'AG' and not (exclude_constitutive and nucX.exclude_constitutive):
                if bground_nameX is not None and bground_nameY is not None:
                    valX = nucX.mutation_rate-back_nucX.mutation_rate
                    valY = nucY.mutation_rate-back_nucY.mutation_rate
                else:
                    valX = nucX.mutation_rate
                    valY = nucY.mutation_rate
                if valX>0 and valY>0:
                    x.append(valX)
                    y.append(valY)
    plot.scatter(x, y, color=color, s=2)
    rho, p = stats.spearmanr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    r, p = stats.pearsonr(np.log10(np.array(x)), np.log10(np.array(y)))
    if bground_nameX is not None and bground_nameY is not None:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s-%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameX, bground_nameX))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s-%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY, bground_nameY))
    else:
        plot.set_xlabel("%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameX))
        plot.set_ylabel("%s mutation fraction" % (lib_nameY))
    plot.set_yscale('log')
    plot.set_xscale('log')
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.annotate('rho=%.3f, r=%.3f, n=%d' % (rho, r, len(x)), xy=(.00002, 1), xytext=(.00002, 1))
    plot.set_xlim(.000001,5)
    plot.set_ylim(.000001,5)

import scipy.stats as stats
import math
import numpy

lib_names = [ '9_70S_0_05uM_onc112_UV_NAz', '10_70S_0_25uM_onc112_UV_NAz', '11_70S_1uM_onc112_UV_NAz', '12_70S_5uM_onc112_UV_NAz']

def make_sig_change_calls(lib_name):
    library = ecoli_batch2_datasets.get_lib_from_name(lib_name)
    #compute normalization factors
    exp_mutations = []
    ctrl_mutations = []
    for rRNA_name in library.rRNA_mutation_data.keys():
        for rRNA_position in sorted(library.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides.keys()):
            nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
            if nuc.identity in 'AG':
                exp_mutations.append(nuc.mutation_rate)
                ctrl_mutations.append(nuc.get_control_nucleotide().mutation_rate)
    exp_norm = numpy.mean(exp_mutations)
    ctrl_norm = numpy.mean(ctrl_mutations)
    
    protections = {}
    deprotections = {}
    for rRNA_name in library.rRNA_mutation_data.keys():
        positions = []
        reactivity_deltas = []
        z_factors = []
        for rRNA_position in sorted(library.rRNA_mutation_data[rRNA_name].nucleotides.keys()):
            nuc = library.get_nucleotide(rRNA_name, rRNA_position)
            if nuc.identity in 'AG' and not nuc.exclude_constitutive:
                positions.append(rRNA_position)
                control_sub=(nuc.mutation_rate/exp_norm) - (nuc.get_control_nucleotide().mutation_rate/ctrl_norm)
                reactivity_deltas.append(control_sub)
                exp_error = nuc.get_error()/exp_norm
                ctrl_error = nuc.get_control_nucleotide().get_error()/ctrl_norm
                z = 1-(1.99*(exp_error+ctrl_error)/abs(control_sub))
                z_factors.append(z)
        reactivity_delta_mean = numpy.mean(reactivity_deltas)
        reactivity_delta_std = numpy.std(reactivity_deltas)
        scores = (numpy.array(reactivity_deltas)-reactivity_delta_mean)/reactivity_delta_std
        protections[rRNA_name] = [positions[i] for i in range(len(positions)) if abs(scores[i])>0 and z_factors[i]>0 and reactivity_deltas[i]<0]
        deprotections[rRNA_name] = [positions[i] for i in range(len(positions)) if abs(scores[i])>0 and z_factors[i]>0 and reactivity_deltas[i]>0]
    return protections, deprotections

all_prot_calls = {}
all_deprot_calls = {}
for lib_name in lib_names:
   all_prot_calls[lib_name], all_deprot_calls[lib_name] = make_sig_change_calls(lib_name)

    source = ColumnDataSource(data=dict(x = x, y = y, label = anno))
    prot_source = ColumnDataSource(data=dict(x = pro_x, y = pro_y, label = pro_anno))
    deprot_source = ColumnDataSource(data=dict(x = depro_x, y = depro_y, label = depro_anno))
    TOOLS = "pan,wheel_zoom,reset,save,hover"
    PlotFig = figure(x_axis_label = "average mutation counts",
                     y_axis_label = "mutation rate fold change",
                     y_axis_type="log", x_axis_type="log", title=sample_name, tools=TOOLS, toolbar_location="right")
    PlotFig.circle("x", "y", size = 5, source=source, color=mod_utils.bokeh_black)
    PlotFig.circle("x", "y", size = 5, source=prot_source, color=mod_utils.bokeh_vermillion)
    PlotFig.circle("x", "y", size = 5, source=deprot_source, color=mod_utils.bokeh_bluishGreen)
    #PlotFig.x_range = Range1d(start=0.00001, end=1)
    PlotFig.y_range = Range1d(start=1/15., end=15.)

    #adjust what information you get when you hover over it
    Hover = PlotFig.select(dict(type=HoverTool))
    Hover.tooltips = OrderedDict([("nuc", "@label")])
    plot_figs.append(PlotFig)
#p = gridplot(plot_figs)

show(gridplot(children=plot_figs, ncols=2, plot_width=400, plot_height=400), notebook_handle=True)
